#      alpha  p-value
#     
def alpha_pvalue(alpha, p_value):
    if p_value >= alpha:
        print(f'\n   {alpha*100}%      :')
        print(f'c  {(1-alpha)*100}%    .')
    if p_value < alpha:
        print(f'\n   {alpha*100}%      :')
        print(f'c  {(1-alpha)*100}%    .')

alpha_pvalue(0.01, res[1])

In [24]:
#     
def make_features(df, max_lag, rolling_mean_size_list):
    # co ,      ..,  
    df['dayofweek'] = df.index.dayofweek
    df['day'] = df.index.day
    
    #     
    for lag in range(1, max_lag + 1):
        df['lag_{}'.format(lag)] = df['num_orders'].shift(lag)
    
    #     
    for i in rolling_mean_size_list:
        df['rolling_mean_{}'.format(i)] = (df['num_orders']
                                .rolling(i, closed='left')
                                .mean())

make_features(resample_hour, 50, [12, 24, 48])
